    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about needing an escrow account for this house i'm looking at in toronto. i've never bought a place before so i'm kinda lost. can u explain what escrow actually is and why it's even used in the closing process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An escrow account is a separate bank account managed by a third-party holder, typically an escrow agent or a lender, to hold funds for specific purposes during a real estate transaction. In Canadian real estate, the escrow account is used to manage various expenses, such as property taxes, insurance, andHomeowners Association (HOA) fees. When you sign a contract of purchase, you deposit funds into the escrow account, and the agent disburses the funds on a predetermined schedule. This helps ensure that these ongoing expenses are paid on time, shielding your finances from potential delays.",
      "source": "target",
